ps he doesn't want to find out if his is one of the ten percent of the motors that will burn up.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You should also be aware of an 'electrician' in NY a few years ago who hooked up a dimmer switch to a 'non rated' ceiling fan.&amp;nbsp; He tested it and it worked, so he left the house.&amp;nbsp; A few hours later, the fan overheated and shorted out, catching the house on fire and killed two children.&amp;nbsp; He was charged with 2nd degree murder, later reduced to manslaughter and sentenced to ten years in prison.&amp;nbsp; He also has to live with the fact that he killed two kids.&amp;nbsp; Electricity is not to be fooled with and it's the reason we have codes.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>12501781</next>\n<prev>12501131</prev>\n<first>12379669</first>\n<last>12578952</last>\n<when>1272943550</when>\n<utime>05/04/10 06:25 AM</utime>\n</post>"}